com.google.inject.commands.intercepting
Class InterceptingInjectorBuilder

java.lang.Object
  com.google.inject.commands.intercepting.InterceptingInjectorBuilder

public final class InterceptingInjectorBuilder
extends Object

Builds an Injector that intercepts provision.

The injector contains an extra binding for Set<Key> annotated with the name "Interceptable". This bound set contains all intercepted keys.

Limitations of the current implementation

All intercepted bindings must have binding targets - for example, a type that is bound to itself cannot be intercepted: 

bind(MyServiceClass.class);

All intercepted bindings must be bound explicitly. Interception cannot be applied to implicit bindings, or bindings that depend on @ProvidedBy, @ImplementedBy annotations.

Implementation note: To intercept provision, an additional, internal binding is created for each intercepted key. This is used to bind the original (non-intercepted) provisioning strategy, and an intercepting binding is created for the original key. This shouldn't have any side-effects on the behaviour of the injector, but may confuse tools that depend on Injector.getBindings() and similar methods.
